            <h2>Capstone Project</h2>
            <div class="project">
                <h3>Home Design App</h3>
                <p>The Home Design App is an Android application that allows users to explore, purchase, and visualize furniture in their homes using Augmented Reality (AR) technology. The app provides users with a rich experience by integrating Firebase for authentication, Firestore for real-time data management, and AR for immersive furniture placement.</p>
                <button onclick="toggleDetails('capstone')">Show More</button>
                <p id="capstone" class="hidden">
                    <strong>Objective:</strong> To create a comprehensive home design solution where users can explore and visualize furniture in their own spaces using AR.<br>
                    <strong>Skills Demonstrated:</strong> Android development (Kotlin), Firebase integration, Firestore real-time database, Augmented Reality (AR), and UI/UX design.<br>
                    <strong>Challenges:</strong> Managing real-time data updates for multiple users and implementing smooth AR functionality were significant challenges, solved using Firebase's real-time capabilities and ARCore integration.<br>
                    <strong>Significance:</strong> This project demonstrates my expertise in building a feature-rich Android application with real-time data and augmented reality, culminating my learning in the Mobile Application Development (MAPD) program.
                </p>
            </div>
